com.conceptwave.scripting
Class Catalog

com.conceptwave.scripting.Object
  com.conceptwave.scripting.CWScriptable
      com.conceptwave.scripting.Catalog

public class Catalog
extends CWScriptable

Once Catalog is initialized, there is one and only one instance of it created. It's referred to as theCatalog. For example, to call the createBasket() method, please follow the syntax theCatalog.createBasket().

browse

public String[] browse(String query,
                       com.conceptwave.scripting.Object[] params)
Deprecated. as of 5.1. SP2 Use runQuery API instead.

Browses the Catalog. The objects that constitute context of the catalog rules - the basket, the inventory and the Catalog context object must be set before the browse API is invoked. The browse API allow search of the Catalog hierarchy, item properties, and attributes value, item to item associations and item prices (charge type associations). The result of the API is a list of pairs of item code & hierarchy node codes. The API is provided for backward compatibility with version 5.0 of the ConceptWave Catalog product and should not be used in new development as it has limited functionality, is slower and need more memory than the recommended "runQuery" API.

Parameters:
query - The Catalog query specification as defined in the documentation
params - Search values for each question mark place holder in the query string as scanned from left to right. Each parameter can be atomic string, number, date or Boolean value or array of strings or numbers. If array it must contain values of the same type - i.e. type (strings or numbers).
Returns:
Array of strings representing pairs of item code and hierarchy node code. The node code may be null.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - DE9256 if there are compilation errors

getItemVersion

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Object[] getItemVersion(String itemCode,
                                                         Date timeStamp)
Gets an available item version by code for a given date. If the item does not exist at that date returns null. If item is expired for given date, return last item version. If item is not available for given date, return first item version.

Parameters:
itemCode - The item code
timeStamp - The request time stamp (date)
Returns:
Null or object list which contains item object and warning message.
  • If the item does not exist, return null
  • If there is available version for given date, return list, 1st element is available item version object.
  • If item is expired for given date, return list, 1st element is last version of item, 2rd element is waning message
  • If No active version for given date, return list, 1st element is first version of item, 2rd element is waning message

    runQuery

    public CatalogQueryResult runQuery(Basket theBasket,
                                   Basket theInventory,
                                   com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean throwCompilerErrors,
                                   String query,
                                   com.conceptwave.scripting.Object[] params)
    Runs a Catalog query. The objects that constitute context of the catalog rules - the basket, the inventory and the Catalog context object must be set before the API is invoked or given as parameters to the API. Catalog queries allow search of Catalog hierarchies, item properties, and attribute values, item to item associations and item prices (charge type associations). The result of the query is a Catalog Query Result object.

    Parameters:
    theBasket - The user basket or null. If null the value set in the Catalog context will be used
    theInventory - The user inventory or null. If null the value set in the Catalog context will be used
    throwCompilerErrors - If true the API will throw exception DE9256 if there are compiler errors, which happens if there are errors in the query syntax.
    query - The Catalog query specification string as defined in the documentation
    params - Search values for each question mark place holder in the query string as scanned from left to right. Each parameter can be atomic string, number, date or Boolean value or array of strings or numbers. If array it must contain values of the same data type (i.e. strings or numbers).
    Returns:
    The catalog query result object.
    Notes: this function returns null if the hierarchy that the query is being run on does not contain any item. Otherwise, if will return a non-null result object, even when the object does not contain any items (i.e. when none of the items in the hierarchy satisfy the query criteria).
